wikimedia-globalblocking-blockedtext-aut:
A message shown to a user when they are using an IP that has been [[mw:Extension:GlobalBlocking|globally autoblocked]] whilst trying to edit.

Refers to:
* {{msg-mw|globalblocking-blockedtext-autoblock-intro}}
* {{msg-mw|blockedtext-made-by}}
* {{msg-mw|blockedtext-reason-comment}}
* {{msg-mw|blockedtext-start-time}}
* {{msg-mw|blockedtext-expiration-time}}
 * {{msg-mw|blockedtext-intended-blockee}}
* {{msg-mw|globalblocking-blockedtext-blocker-admin}}
* {{msg-mw|globalblocking-blockedtext-email-feature}}
* {{msg-mw|blockedtext-block-ip}}
* {{msg-mw|blockedtext-block-id}}
* {{msg-mw|blockedtext-include-details-queries}}

Parameters:
* $1 - The user to be executed
* $2 - The reason for the block
* $3 - The current IP address of the blocked user
* $4 - (Unused) the blocking sysop's username (plain text, without the link)
* $5 - The unique numeric identifier of the block
* $6 - The expiry of the block
* $7 - the intended target of the block (what the blocking user specified in the blocking form)
* $8 - The timestamp when the block started

